			"text":"### Budget Line:\n\n- The **budget line** shows the possible combinations of two goods a consumer can afford given their income and the prices of those goods.\n- The slope of the budget line represents the ratio of the prices of the two goods.\n- **Key Concept**: The consumer chooses a combination of goods on the budget line that maximizes satisfaction, often where the budget line is tangent to the highest possible indifference curve.\n\nLet me know if you would like a visualization of these concepts!",
